## Step 4: Create sketch source resolver

**New file:** `src/modules/sketch/sheets/sketchSources.js`

Exports:
- `resolveSketchViewportSource(sketchProject, viewport)` ‚Äî switch on `viewport.sourceView`:
  - `sketch_assembly_top/front/side` ‚Üí `buildSketchAssemblySource(project, viewport.sourceRefId, view)` ‚Äî gather parts for assembly (or all if null), compute bounds via `projectPartToView` + `getPartsBounds` pattern from `sketchSheetExport.js`, return `{ kind: 'sketch_assembly', view, parts, dimensions, assembly, bounds }`
  - `sketch_part_detail` ‚Üí `buildSketchPartDetailSource(project, viewport.sourceRefId)` ‚Äî find part, compute 3-view L-layout bounds (top+front+side arranged with gaps), auto-generate dimension descriptors for width/depth/height, return `{ kind: 'sketch_part_detail', part, viewLayouts, bounds }`
  - `sketch_part_list` ‚Üí `buildSketchPartListSource(project, viewport.sourceRefId)` ‚Äî build BOM rows from parts, compute table bounds, return `{ kind: 'sketch_part_list', rows, columnWidths, bounds }`
  - default ‚Üí `{ kind: 'empty', ... }`

- `getSketchViewportSourceLabel(sourceView)` ‚Äî returns display labels

Reuses: `projectPartToView`, `getPartExtents` from `../domain/viewProjection.js`; `createDimensionFigure` from `@/annotations/dimensions` for dimension geometry.

