## Step 6: Create sketch sheet viewport content renderer

**New file:** `src/modules/sketch/renderers/SketchSheetViewportContent.jsx`

Handles three source kinds:

- **`sketch_assembly`** ‚Äî renders parts via `PartRenderer` and dimensions via `DimensionRenderer` (both from sketch module) in the given orthographic view. Uses `view={source.view}`, `isSelected={false}`, `zoom={1}`.

- **`sketch_part_detail`** ‚Äî renders three sub-groups positioned per `source.viewLayouts` (top, front, side). Each group: part rect + auto-dimension lines (extension lines, arrowheads, text via `createDimensionFigure`). View labels rendered as `<text>`.

- **`sketch_part_list`** ‚Äî SVG table: header row + data rows. Columns: Item, Name, Type, Material, Qty, Dimensions. Pattern follows `RoofScheduleRenderer`. Uses `SHEET_COLORS` for consistent styling.

Returns `null` for `kind === 'empty'`.

